{"award_age":55.0,"bio_image":"full\/055250cd00ee525b00d238728498228cf3beb6ae.jpg","category":"Economics","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1953-02-28T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/4\/48\/Paul_Krugman-press_conference_Dec_07th%2C_2008-8.jpg\/225px-Paul_Krugman-press_conference_Dec_07th%2C_2008-8.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Krugman","mini_bio":"<p><b>Paul Robin Krugman<\/b> (born February 28, 1953) is an American <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Economist\" title=\"Economist\">economist<\/a>, Professor of Economics and International Affairs at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Woodrow_Wilson_School_of_Public_and_International_Affairs\" title=\"Woodrow Wilson School of Public and International Affairs\">Woodrow Wilson School of Public and International Affairs<\/a> at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Princeton_University\" title=\"Princeton University\">Princeton University<\/a>, Centenary Professor at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/London_School_of_Economics\" title=\"London School of Economics\">London School of Economics<\/a>, Distinguished Scholar at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Luxembourg_Income_Study\" title=\"Luxembourg Income Study\">Luxembourg Income Study<\/a> Center at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_Graduate_Center,_CUNY\" title=\"The Graduate Center, CUNY\">CUNY Graduate Center<\/a>, and a left-leaning <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Op-ed\" title=\"Op-ed\">op-ed<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Columnist\" title=\"Columnist\">columnist<\/a> for <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_New_York_Times\" title=\"The New York Times\">The New York Times<\/a><\/i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Krugman#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-krugmanonline_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Krugman#cite_note-krugmanonline-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> In 2008, Krugman won the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sveriges_Riksbank_Prize_in_Economic_Sciences_in_Memory_of_Alfred_Nobel\" title=\"Sveriges Riksbank Prize in Economic Sciences in Memory of Alfred Nobel\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Sveriges Riksbank Prize in Economic Sciences in Memory of Alfred Nobel<\/a><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Krugman#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> for his contributions to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/New_Trade_Theory\" title=\"New Trade Theory\" class=\"mw-redirect\">New Trade Theory<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Economic_geography\" title=\"Economic geography\">New Economic Geography<\/a>. According to the prize Committee, the prize was given for Krugman's work explaining the patterns of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/International_trade\" title=\"International trade\">international trade<\/a> and the geographic concentration of wealth, by examining the effects of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Economy_of_scale\" title=\"Economy of scale\" class=\"mw-redirect\">economies of scale<\/a> and of consumer preferences for diverse goods and services.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NobelComments_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Krugman#cite_note-NobelComments-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>Krugman is known in academia for his work on <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/International_economics\" title=\"International economics\">international economics<\/a> (including trade theory, economic geography, and international finance),<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Krugman#cite_note-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-forbes131008_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Krugman#cite_note-forbes131008-7\"><span>[<\/span>7<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Liquidity_trap\" title=\"Liquidity trap\">liquidity traps<\/a>, and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Currency_crisis\" title=\"Currency crisis\">currency crisis<\/a>. Krugman is ranked among the most influential economic thinkers in the US.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Krugman#cite_note-8\"><span>[<\/span>8<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> In 2015 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_Economist\" title=\"The Economist\">The Economist<\/a> listed him as the 2nd most influential economist in the world.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Krugman#cite_note-9\"><span>[<\/span>9<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>Krugman has written over 20 books, including scholarly works, textbooks and books for a more general audience, and has published over 200 scholarly articles in professional journals and edited volumes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Krugman#cite_note-10\"><span>[<\/span>10<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He has also written more than 750 columns on economic and political issues for <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_New_York_Times\" title=\"The New York Times\">The New York Times<\/a><\/i>, <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fortune_(magazine)\" title=\"Fortune (magazine)\">Fortune<\/a><\/i> and <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Slate_(magazine)\" title=\"Slate (magazine)\">Slate<\/a><\/i>.<\/p><p>As a commentator, Krugman has written on a wide range of economic issues including <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Income_distribution\" title=\"Income distribution\">income distribution<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Taxation\" title=\"Taxation\" class=\"mw-redirect\">taxation<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Macroeconomics\" title=\"Macroeconomics\">macroeconomics<\/a> and international economics. Krugman considers himself a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Modern_liberalism_in_the_United_States\" title=\"Modern liberalism in the United States\">liberal<\/a>, calling one of his books and his <i>New York Times<\/i> blog <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_Conscience_of_a_Liberal\" title=\"The Conscience of a Liberal\">The Conscience of a Liberal<\/a><\/i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Krugman#cite_note-11\"><span>[<\/span>11<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> His popular commentary has attracted considerable comment, both positive and negative.<sup id=\"cite_ref-economist_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Krugman#cite_note-economist-12\"><span>[<\/span>12<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Paul Krugman","place_of_birth":"Albany, New York, USA","place_of_death":null,"text":"Paul Krugman , Economics, 2008","year":2008.0}